snippet.textDisplay: If vlog style Creators on YT have mostly migrated to the “ its real, but sometimes we do retakes to get it on camera vibe.. with the unspoken yet universally accepted truth that it’s not real but we can pretend, because it’s not as bad as reality tv, why then add another level of replay on tv when we all know we just watched the same  reality retake in the vlog last week, last month, last year? I enjoy the interview sessions, and I understand they would require context for either older stuff, or new viewers, but why not have Tana work with a crew film her vlogs and then have MTV have the opportunity to replay the scenes either edited or in sequence of the storyline and add the interview layer? We all know everyone of these scenes are painfully obviously fake and contrived, and super disingenuous to the actual people.
